<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-380-976  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 380 976.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  April 23 1990 v218 n17 p9(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Argentine telco sale causes uproar. (News of the Week )</TITLE><AUTHOR>Luxner, Larry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Argentine Pres Carlos Menem wants to privatize his country'santiquated telephone system.andP;  He wants to sell 60 percent ofEmpresa Nacional de Telecommunicaciones (Entel) to outsideinvestors and 10 percent to Entel employees, with the remaining 30percent to be sold in a public offering.andP;  The entire process wouldbe completed by Oct 8, 1990.andP;  Unions already have organized a24-hour work stoppage that shut down Argentina's communications,and the unions vow to stage more strikes - as well as acts ofsabotage - to protest the sale.andP;  But Pres Menem says he will notback down, and polls indicate that 80 percent of the Argentinepeople supports Menem's move to privatize what Nicholas Tozer,editor of the English-language Buenos Aires Herald calls 'the mostcorrupt telephone company in the world.'andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Empresa Nacional de Telecomunicaciones (Argentina) (management).andO;Topic:     ArgentinaTelephone companiesPrivatizationPolitical Issues.andO;Person:    Menem, Carlos Saul (telecommunication policy).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>